<p>I am trying to send a string to a pipe in unix. When I go through a line-by-line debugging process, the call mkfifo() creates the file in the same directory as the source code. However, when I reach the open() call, the debugger is no longer able to proceed. I'm not sure why it is unable to access the pipe file. </p>  <p>Here's the code in question: </p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;fcntl.h&gt; #include &lt;sys/stat.h&gt; #include &lt;sys/types.h&gt; #include &lt;unistd.h&gt;  int main() { int fd; char * myfifo = "myfifo";  /* create the FIFO (named pipe) */ mkfifo(myfifo, 0666);  /* write "Hi" to the FIFO */ fd = open(myfifo, O_WRONLY); write(fd, "Hi", sizeof("Hi")); close(fd);  /* remove the FIFO */ unlink(myfifo);  return 0; } </code></pre>  <p>Any suggestions are appreciated. Thank you.</p>